== Symbol resolution ==
PC 0x801E2F10 → vmlinux offset 0x1E2F10 → put_dec_trunc8 + 0xAC
                (function symbol at 0x001E2E64)
Disassembly excerpt:
  1e2f04: mulhu  a5,a4,a5      <-- multi-cycle iterative MUL/DIV FU
  1e2f08: mul    a1,a5,a2      <-- multi-cycle (a2=100, a5=mulhu result)
  1e2f0c: sub    a4,a4,a1
  1e2f10: slli   a4,a4,0x1     <-- HUNG HERE

== Hypothesis ==
Core_pc frozen at 0x801E2F10 (slli) means the F-stage's pcFetchS is held
ahead-of-X. With our 1-cycle BRAM read latency, X must be at PC 0x1E2F0C
(sub) or earlier. If X is stuck on the `mul a1, a5, a2` at 0x1E2F0C, the
M-extension iterative FU (`Riski5.Core.FU.MulDiv.mulDivFUIterative`)
might be stuck in MdBusyMul k phase forever. That would assert
`mdBusyS=True` permanently, freezing pcFetchS at the next-PC after mul
(= 0x1E2F10 = slli) and stopping all instruction commits.

The bridge IS firing (master cycles MIdle ↔ MBusy and slave processes),
but useful work doesn't progress. Bridge is innocent here — the issue
is upstream in the core's M-extension.
